The paper discusses data management in networked industrial environments, which involves the use of information and communication technologies in industrial and manufacturing systems. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI) as well as databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses architectural designs and data-centric services, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper identifies open research challenges for the future, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
